    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1871-07-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1871-07-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="250" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d250">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 229.</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Pakenham</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                            Fish</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1871-07-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi>
                                27, 1871</date>. (Received July 28.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have been instructed by Earl Granville to
                        inform the Government of the United States that Her Majesty’s government
                        have appointed Mr. Russell Gurney, recorder of London, to be British claims
                        commissioner, and I accordingly lose no time in acquainting you with the
                        fact of the above nomination.</p>
                <p>I have the honor, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>F. J. PAKENHAM.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
